<span id="Description"></span>
==Opis==

Narzędzie '''Clarify Selection''' wyświetla menu wypisujące pobliskie obiekty geometryczne różnych typów obok kursora podczas najeżdżania nim na model.

[[File:ClarifySelection.gif]]

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Użycie==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Place the cursor over geometry in the [[3D_View|3D View]].
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Clarify Selection}} option from the context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|G}} then {{KEY|G}}.
# A menu with listing object types appears next to the cursor. Depending on the objects near the cursor, it may include:
#* Objects
#* Faces
#* Edges
#* Vertices
#* Other
# Choose an object type.
# Move the cursor over the submenu that appears. Hovered submenu items are highlighted in the 3D View.
# Click an item to select it.
</div>


